= GrowthRing =
''This software is heavily under development.''

'''GrowthRing''' visualizes how a document grows over revisions.
It contains:
* a multiple sequence alignment tool for texts, written in Scala.
* an interactive demo, deployable at Google App Engine or other servlet-compatible environment.

== How to use ==

=== Using the multiple sequence aligner ===
# sbt one-jar # use sbt 0.12
# java -Xss50M -jar target/scala-2.9.2/growthring_2.9.2-0.1-one-jar.jar < sample_input.txt | dot /dev/stdin -Tpdf -o sample_output.pdf

=== Using the anonymizer ===
# sbt publish # use sbt 0.12
# cd growthring-web && mvn package && sh dev_appserver.sh target/growthring-web-0.1 # use maven 3
# xdg-open http://localhost:8080

=== Combining with SAIS ===
# Use the command below to get the shared library version of SAIS.
 gcc -shared sais.o -o libsais.so 
# Put libsais.so into anywhere written in LD_LIBRARY_PATH.

